{"questionId":"19960","questionHtml":"<p>Given the width of a pixel is approximately <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>025</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, find the number of squares in the final image.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>025</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A</strong></em><em><strong>1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>160</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A</strong></em><em><strong>1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept equations in place of inequalities.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Hence there are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math> squares&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong></em><em><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19960","referenceCode":"EXN.3.AHL.TZ0.2b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given the width of a pixel is approximately 0.025 cm, find the number of squares in the final image.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}